applicationVersions.description: This application is responsible for cargo management .
AirOps systems is resposible for complex management of flight scheduling and trip oversight, crew compliance and communication, customer data, charter and maintenance .
This applications takes care of operations around Baggage handling like belt allocation etc. .
ACARS-Aircraft Communications Addressing and Reporting System is a digital datalink system for transmission of short messages between aircraft and ground stations via airband radio or satellite.
Ramp handling is defined as service ( load, unload , move baggage & cargo )for the aircraft while it is on the ground (after arrival and before departure).
Devices that emit out real time location coordinates.

eventVersions.description:
{PNR}    = PNR generated for passenger
{dep}     = Departure airport
{arrival} = Arrival airport
{class}   = booking class - Y for economy and J for business class

schemaVersions.content:
<?xml version = "1.0" encoding = "UTF-8"?>
<xs:schema xmlns:xs = "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
<xs:import namespace="http://www.fixm.aero/flight/4.2" schemaLocation="../../core/flight/Flight.xsd"/>
   <xs:element name = "contact">
      <xs:complexType>
            <xs:element name = "flightNo" type = "xs:string" />
            <xs:element name = "noOfPax" type = "xs:int" />
            <xs:element name = "noOfBaggage" type = "xs:int" />
      </xs:complexType>
   </xs:element>
</xs:schema>
